registry.title: Objects
registry.note:
In accordance with Sections 7 and 7.1 of , proposed registrations must be submitted to a mailing list for review by IESG-designated experts.
Objects are listed in alphabetic order. The specifications that define objects also define operations and attributes for the objects.

registry.title: Attributes
registry.note:
In accordance with Sections 7 and 7.2 of , proposed registrations must be submitted to a mailing list for review by IESG-designated experts.
Attributes are listed in alphabetic order. The member attributes of collection attributes are indented two spaces immediately after the collection attribute to which they belong.
The "xxx" Job Template attributes are Job object attributes, while the "xxx-default" and "xxx-supported" Job Template attributes are Printer object attributes. See Section 5.2 Job Template Attributes.
The "xxx" Subscription Template attributes are Subscription object attributes, while the "xxx-default" and "xxx-supported" Subscription Template attributes are Printer object attributes.â€ See Section 5.2 Subscription Template Attributes.

registry.title: Enum Attribute Values
registry.note: In accordance with Sections 7 and 7.4 of , proposed registrations must be submitted to a mailing list for review by IESG-designated experts.

registry.title: Attribute Group Tags
registry.note:
Attribute Group Tags, Out-of-Band Attribute Value Tags, and Attribute Syntaxes share the same number space.
In accordance with Sections 7 and 7.5 of , proposed registrations must be submitted to a mailing list for review by IESG-designated experts.
The range of Attribute Group Tags is 0x00 to 0x0F. See Section 3.5.1. The tag values are listed in numeric order.

registry.title: Out-of-Band Attribute Value Tags
registry.note:
Attribute Group Tags, Out-of-Band Attribute Value Tags, and Attribute Syntaxes share the same number space.
In accordance with Sections 7 and 7.6 of , proposed registrations must be submitted to a mailing list for review by IESG-designated experts.
The range of out-of-band tags is 0x10 to 0x1F. See Section 3.5.2. The tag values are listed in numeric order.

registry.title: Attribute Syntaxes
registry.note:
Attribute Group Tags, Out-of-Band Attribute Value Tags, and Attribute Syntaxes share the same number space.
In accordance with Sections 7 and 7.7 of , proposed registrations must be submitted to a mailing list for review by IESG-designated experts.
The range of attribute syntaxes is 0x20 to 0xFF. Use of the 0x7F value permits additional values up to 0x3FFFFFFF for Specification Required action and 0x40000000 to 0x7FFFFFFF for vendor extensions. See Section 3.5.2. The tag values are listed in numeric order.

registry.title: Operations
registry.note:
In accordance with Sections 7 and 7.8 of , proposed registrations must be submitted to a mailing list for review by IESG-designated experts.
See the hex values assigned to each operation under the "operations-supported" attribute in Section 4 above. In addition, vendors may define their own private operations. See the explanation at the beginning of Section 4 above on the enum allocation for such vendor-defined private operations.
Operations are listed in alphabetic order. Specifications that extend the semantics of operations defined in other specifications will be listed here as well on separate lines with the notation "(extension)" after the name.

registry.title: Status Codes
registry.note:
In accordance with Sections 7 and 7.9 of , proposed registrations must be submitted to a mailing list for review by IESG-designated experts.
The range of status code values is 0x0000 to 0x7FFF. Appendix B of allocates the value ranges for each status code class as follows:
"successful" - 0x0000 to 0x00FF "informational" - 0x0100 to 0x01FF Unassigned - 0x0200 to 0x02FF "redirection" - 0x0300 to 0x03FF "client-error" - 0x0400 to 0x04FF "server-error" - 0x0500 to 0x05FF Unassigned - 0x0600 to 0x7FFF
The top half (128 values) of each range (0x0n80 to 0x0nFF, for n = 0 to 5) is reserved for vendor use within each status code class. Status codes are listed in numeric order.
